<paragraph blockId="41.[285,1023,350,407]" box="[564,698,383,407]" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">
(
<figureCitation box="[572,690,383,407]" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="41.[125,185,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,877,1549]" captionTargetId="figure-146@41.[170,1128,877,1549]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 23. Amiota (Amiota) wuyishanensis Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopod and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657951/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">Figure 23</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[125,1172,461,549]" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis box="[125,239,461,485]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Parameres slightly sclerotized, distally with two pointed processes (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="41.[125,185,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,877,1549]" captionTargetId="figure-146@41.[170,1128,877,1549]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 23. Amiota (Amiota) wuyishanensis Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopod and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657951/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">Figure 23C, D</figureCitation>
), inter-laterally with one triangular process and one knot-like process having four sensilla.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[125,245,606,630]" box="[125,245,606,630]" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis box="[125,245,606,630]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[125,1172,655,714]" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis box="[125,193,655,679]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">Wing.</emphasis>
Wing with 24–26 minute, peg-like spinules on ventral surface of costal vein between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[145,178,697,714]" fontSize="7" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[258,291,697,714]" fontSize="7" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">4+5</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[125,1172,752,841]" lastBlockId="42.[138,1185,136,288]" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="305" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis box="[125,308,752,776]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium separated laterally at mid-dorsal portion, with 
<emphasis box="[991,1015,753,776]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">ca</emphasis>
23 setae near posterior to ventral margins (
<figureCitation box="[491,637,785,809]" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="41.[125,185,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,877,1549]" captionTargetId="figure-146@41.[170,1128,877,1549]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 23. Amiota (Amiota) wuyishanensis Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopod and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657951/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="304">Figure 23A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus pubescent, slightly expanded at posteroventral corner, medially with three setae, with eight prensisetae on distal margin, and many setae on ventral margin and outer mesal surface. Gonopods separated medially, sclerotized medially, each with three finger-like, apical processes and two sclerotized lateral processes (
<figureCitation box="[371,526,200,224]" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="41.[125,185,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,877,1549]" captionTargetId="figure-146@41.[170,1128,877,1549]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 23. Amiota (Amiota) wuyishanensis Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopod and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657951/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="305">Figure 23C</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus fused to paramere (
<figureCitation box="[966,1171,200,224]" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="41.[125,185,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,877,1549]" captionTargetId="figure-146@41.[170,1128,877,1549]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 23. Amiota (Amiota) wuyishanensis Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopod and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657951/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="305">Figure 23D, E</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme: apical plate with four pits on each lateral margin; stalk thick, long (
<figureCitation box="[146,284,264,288]" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="41.[125,185,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,877,1549]" captionTargetId="figure-146@41.[170,1128,877,1549]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 23. Amiota (Amiota) wuyishanensis Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopod and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657951/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="305">Figure 23F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
